'''Xin''' (辛, kanoto) is the 8th of the {{ill|Heavenly Stems|lt=Ten Heavenly Stems|8=en|ja|十干|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}.<ref>https://www.bing.com/ck/a?!&&p=b9acbea8f83e27ae0c68a195cdb688ae8b48eddc1dd0e41d7f1001021b5a674aJmltdHM9MTc0MzAzMzYwMA&ptn=3&ver=2&hsh=4&fclid=3e6f989f-7779-62d7-1cd7-8d247648633d&psq=Kanoto+(%e8%be%9b)&u=a1aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cudGFub3NoaWlqYXBhbmVzZS5jb20vZGljdGlvbmFyeS9lbnRyeV9kZXRhaWxzLmNmbT9lbnRyeV9pZD01NjAwMg&ntb=1</ref>

== Overview ==
* The origin of the character "辛" has been subject to various proposals, but no definitive theory exists. Its usage to denote the eighth position in the Ten Heavenly Stems is through {{ill|Jia Jie|ja|仮借|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}.
* Years ending in the digit 1 in the {{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|西暦|1=Common Era|2=ja|3=西暦|4=zh|5=公元|6=es|7=Era común|8=nl|9=Gangbare jaartelling|10=simple|11=Common Era|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} correspond to the year of Xin. Additionally, the alternate name for the year is '''Chongguang''' ({{ill|重光|ja|重光|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}})<ref>{{Cite web |title=Dictionary View [重光 : ㄔㄨㄥˋ ㄍㄨㄤ] |url=https://dict.revised.moe.edu.tw/dictView.jsp?ID=126821&la=0&powerMode=0 |website=Ministry of Education Revised Chinese Dictionary 2021 |access-date=2024-03-08 |language=zh-Hant-TW|qq=}}</ref>.
* In {{ill|Chinese chemical nomenclature|ja|化合物命名法|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}, the term "Xin" is used in the names of compounds or functional groups containing eight {{ill|carbon atoms|ja|炭素|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}, such as {{ill|Octane|ja|オクタン|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} and {{ill|Octyl group|ja|オクチル基|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}.
* The opposite stem is {{ill|Bing|ja|丙|1=Hinoe (丙)|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} (hinoe).
* The {{ill|lucky direction|ja|恵方|3=歳徳神|1=Toshitoku-shin|lt=Lucky direction|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} associated with Xin is slightly south of south-southeast (165 degrees).

