==Pronunciation== ==Years of Kanoto (辛)== * Chinese (Pinyin): Xīn * Korean: Sin (신) * Vietnamese: Tân * Japanese: ** On’yomi: Shin (しん) ** Kunyomi (elemental): Kanoto (かのと, 金の弟 – “Younger Metal”) ==Months of Kanoto (辛)== == Overview == * The origin of the character "辛" has been subject to various proposals, but no definitive theory exists. Its usage to denote the eighth position in the Ten Heavenly Stems is through {{ill|Jia Jie|ja|仮借|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Jia Jie|qq=}}. * Years ending in the digit 1 in the [[:en:Common Era|Common Era]] correspond to the year of Xin. Additionally, the alternate name for the year is '''Chongguang''' ({{ill|重光|ja|重光|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/重光|qq=}})<ref>{{Cite web |title=Dictionary View [重光 : ㄔㄨㄥˋ ㄍㄨㄤ] |url=https://dict.revised.moe.edu.tw/dictView.jsp?ID=126821&la=0&powerMode=0 |website=Ministry of Education Revised Chinese Dictionary 2021 |access-date=2024-03-08 |language=zh-Hant-TW|qq=}}</ref>. * In {{ill|Chinese chemical nomenclature|ja|化合物命名法|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Chinese chemical nomenclature|qq=}}, the term "Xin" is used in the names of compounds or functional groups containing eight [[:en:Carbon|carbon atoms]], such as [[:en:Octane|Octane]] and {{ill|Octyl group|ja|オクチル基|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Octyl group|qq=}}. * The opposite stem is {{ill|Bing|ja|丙|1=Hinoe (丙)|lt=Hinoe (丙)|2=ja|3=丙|4=zh|5=丙|1=Hinoe (丙)|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Bing|13=User:Immanuelle/Hinoe (丙)|qq=}} (hinoe). * The {{ill|lucky direction|ja|恵方|3=歳徳神|1=Toshitoku-shin|lt=Lucky direction|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/lucky direction|13=User:Immanuelle/Toshitoku-shin|qq=}} associated with Xin is slightly south of south-southeast (165 degrees). ==Days of Kanoto (辛)== ==Sexagenary cycles containing Kanoto (辛)== {{Wiktionary|辛|1=Kanoto (辛)|lt=Kanoto (辛)|2=ja|3=辛|4=zh|5=辛|1=Kanoto (辛)|qq=}}
