{{Ten Heavenly Stems and Earthly Branches}}

'''Kanoto''' (辛, kanoto) is the 8th of the {{ill|Heavenly Stems|en|Heavenly Stems|qid=Q1190985|lt=Ten Heavenly Stems|1=Heavenly Stems}}.<ref>https://www.bing.com/ck/a?!&&p=b9acbea8f83e27ae0c68a195cdb688ae8b48eddc1dd0e41d7f1001021b5a674aJmltdHM9MTc0MzAzMzYwMA&ptn=3&ver=2&hsh=4&fclid=3e6f989f-7779-62d7-1cd7-8d247648633d&psq=Kanoto+(%e8%be%9b)&u=a1aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cudGFub3NoaWlqYXBhbmVzZS5jb20vZGljdGlvbmFyeS9lbnRyeV9kZXRhaWxzLmNmbT9lbnRyeV9pZD01NjAwMg&ntb=1</ref>

== Pronunciations: 辛 (Stem 8) ==
* Chinese (Pinyin): Xīn  
* Korean: Sin (신)  
* Vietnamese: Tân  
* Japanese:  
** On’yomi: Shin (しん)  
** Kunyomi (elemental): Kanoto (かのと, 金の弟 – “Younger Metal”)

== Overview ==
* The origin of the character "辛" has been subject to various proposals, but no definitive theory exists. Its usage to denote the eighth position in the Ten Heavenly Stems is through {{ill|Jia Jie|ja|仮借|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Jia Jie|1=Loangraph|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q10888485}}.
* Years ending in the digit 1 in the {{ill|Common Era|en|Common Era|qid=Q208141|lt=Common Era|1=Common Era}} correspond to the year of Xin. Additionally, the alternate name for the year is '''Chongguang''' ({{ill|重光|ja|重光|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/重光|1=Q11644697|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q11644697}})<ref>{{Cite web |title=Dictionary View [重光 : ㄔㄨㄥˋ ㄍㄨㄤ] |url=https://dict.revised.moe.edu.tw/dictView.jsp?ID=126821&la=0&powerMode=0 |website=Ministry of Education Revised Chinese Dictionary 2021 |access-date=2024-03-08 |language=zh-Hant-TW|qq=}}</ref>.
* In {{ill|Chinese chemical nomenclature|ja|化合物命名法|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Chinese chemical nomenclature|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to IUPAC命名法|1=IUPAC nomenclature of chemistry|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q20826683}}, the term "Xin" is used in the names of compounds or functional groups containing eight {{ill|Carbon|en|Carbon|qid=Q623|lt=carbon atoms|1=Carbon}}, such as {{ill|Octane|en|Octane|qid=Q150681|lt=Octane|1=Octane}} and {{ill|Octyl group|ja|オクチル基|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Octyl group|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}.
* The opposite stem is {{ill|Bing|ja|丙|1=Hinoe (丙)|lt=Hinoe (丙)|2=ja|3=丙|4=zh|5=丙|1=Hinoe (丙)|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Bing|13=User:Immanuelle/Hinoe (丙)|qq=}} (hinoe).
* The {{ill|lucky direction|ja|恵方|3=歳徳神|1=Toshitoku-shin|lt=Lucky direction|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/lucky direction|13=User:Immanuelle/Toshitoku-shin|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 歳徳神}} associated with Xin is slightly south of south-southeast (165 degrees).

